parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition coil can cause engine misfires, loud noises, and a burning odor, which can lead to engine damage, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially cause accidents due to loss of power.
symptoms: loud noise when starting the engine
burning odor coming from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, such as the engine stalling, air conditioning issues, and windshield wiper malfunctions, which can lead to accidents, inconvenience, and decreased vehicle reliability.
symptoms: air conditioning causing the engine to cut off
windshield wipers not responding to the switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the automatic sliding door can cause injuries to passengers, especially children, as it may close, latch, and lock unexpectedly, trapping them.
The cracked vinyl covering on the instrument panel around the airbag compartment may cause a risk of inadvertent airbag deployment, leading to unexpected injuries.
symptoms: Cracked vinyl covering on the instrument panel around the airbag compartment

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The airbag system malfunction can lead to a false sense of security, as the airbag may not deploy in the event of an accident, potentially causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: The dashboard displays an "Airbag Problem" warning message
the airbag system fails to function properly
the vehicle's computer system logs an error code related to the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty airbag sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to unnecessary deployments or failures to deploy in the event of an accident, potentially causing serious injury or death.
symptoms: the dashboard displays an "Airbag Problem" warning message
the airbag system fails to function properly
the vehicle's computer system logs an error code related to the airbag system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cracked Fuel Line and Ignored Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked fuel line can cause a fuel leak, which can lead to engine fires, accidents, or even fatalities, especially when carrying passengers, including children.
The vehicle's sudden and unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, or near-misses, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward while driving at various speeds
the surging occurs when the cruise control is engaged

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body control can cause the vehicle to surge forward unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-misses, potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward while driving at various speeds
the surging occurs when the cruise control is engaged
